In the exercise, the YTM and the coupon rate are given annually. We need to divide them by two to get a semiannual rate.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{semiannual coupon rate}&=\dfrac{4.9\%}{2}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{2.45\%}
\end{aligned}$$

**The value of the semiannual coupon rate is 2.45\%.**

Now, let's calculate the semiannual YTM of the Weismann Co. bond.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{semiannual YTM}&=\dfrac{4.5\%}{2}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{2.25\%}
\end{aligned}$$

**The value of semiannual YTM is 2.25\%.**
